node.text: Sharing all the tips and behind scenes of prepping and living through a kitchen renovation. Today I’m talking about my Costco staples that will get me through a month without cooking!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jennifer Gizzi on September 08, 2021 tagging @stainmaster. May be an image of 1 person, child and indoor.

node.text: Some days just don’t go as planned.  I had high hopes for today but Atticus had other ideas… I’m sure I’ll miss these days when he’s at home with me so for now I’ll just slow down and enjoy them.  This room has really evolved into a cozy hangout for the boys… always on the floor.  I’m sharing more in stories about this @stainmaster carpet and why I wouldn’t trust any other brand to handle all that life throws at us.  Durability & comfort… yes please. #stainmaster #lowesgoals #lowespartner

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jennifer Gizzi on September 07, 2021 tagging @brickandbatten. May be an image of tree, brick wall and outdoors.

node.text: It’s not a reveal… but I couldn’t help not posting this new view I snapped this morning. The storm door came off and the new lights went up. There’s a fresh post on the blog talking all about my experience using an online design service to visualize our painted brick. If you’re thinking about an exterior renovation, it’s a must read! #exteriorpainting #paintedbrick

Photo by Jennifer Gizzi on September 07, 2021. May be an image of tree and outdoors.
Photo shared by Jennifer Gizzi on September 04, 2021 tagging @stugastudio. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Sharing a different angle of this view because it makes me so so happy. Also… exciting news over in stories today. Spoiler Alert: we got the house!! Talking a little about plans and also the dilemma I’m having with the balusters for this staircase. It’s an exciting day, happy Saturday everyone! Wood flooring: @stugastudio Ingrid #stairs #stairdesign #stuga

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jennifer Gizzi on September 03, 2021 tagging @circalighting. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: New stairs and a new chandelier just took this view up a few notches!! I looked so long for a light that would honor the traditional elements of my home while still giving it a modern vibe.  I needed a fixture that would make a great first impression and set the tone for the rest of the house.  I landed on this beautiful black and antique brass Farlane Chandelier from @circalighting and it did not disappoint.  One step closer to the entryway of my dreams 🖤(also… swipe to see the first video I took of this space!) #entrywaylighting #foyer #circalighting

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jennifer Gizzi on August 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, outdoors and door.

node.text: Faux wood garage door… yes please! I was quoted 7K for new wood garage doors… if all goes right, these will be under $100! One more piece to this exterior renovation is complete. Who’s attempting this DIY? It’s a good one!  #diy #garagedoors #woodgaragedoors

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jennifer Gizzi on August 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, outdoors and door.
Photo by Jennifer Gizzi on August 31, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and brick wall.
Photo by Jennifer Gizzi on August 30, 2021. May be an image of standing, outdoors and tree.

node.text: First phase of our exterior makeover is complete. We painted our outdated red brick and we basically have a new house! Olvin and his crew were amazing and I couldn’t have asked for a better team to handle this awesome project. There’s still some fun parts left out here…. including some faux wood garage doors. Who’s following along? It’s my first time tackling this DIY and I’m super excited to learn and share all my tips. #exteriorpainting #paintedbrick

node.text: I’m not sure I’ve ever been so excited for a reveal in 4 years on the Gram… what about you? #paintedbrick #gizzirenovates

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jennifer Gizzi on August 11, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: Let there be light! We added an egress window to our basement and I’m talking through all the details including cost and benefits over on the blog. My mission here has always been education and I’d love to create more resources to help each of you on your own renovation journey. If you have any requests for renovation topics, please let me know in the comments! Things are in the works 🥰 #renovation #renolife #egresswindow

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jennifer Gizzi on August 06, 2021 tagging @stainmaster. May be an image of bedroom.

node.text: The beginning of Abi June’s princess room!  I might not have this whole room designed just yet but I think the starting point is at a lovely spot (asymmetrical window and all!). We installed this @stainmaster carpet in all of the kids rooms right after moving in. It’s the perfect foundation for just about any design… and functional! We’ve had more than a few accidents with 4 young children… and this carpet has endured.  Are you brave enough for light carpet in a kids room? Come on over to stories and I’ll show you how easily this cleans up!  #partner #stainmaster #lowesgoals #lowespartner

node.text: Wallpaper is done!! 💃 One of those small unfinished projects checked off the list! Not sure if there’s a better to update a rom than a statement wallpaper.  This plaid wallpaper from @brewsterhome was love at first sight for me and helped me turn this space into the ultimate movie-watching room for our little family.  I reached out and they would love to help you guys create a dreamy room of your own!  One winner will receive a wallpaper feature wall of your choice!  Rules are simple… Like this post… comment and tag a wallpaper loving bestie… & follow @brewsterhome !! #sponsored #diywallpaper #wallpapergoals

node.text: Is this my house?  Does this convince anyone that painted brick is a good idea?  Anyone else as floored as I am?  Do you love this new take on the windows? So many questions!  I found @brickandbatten on Pinterest while searching for painted brick house inspiration and I’m so glad I did… They helped me visualize what I had in my head to transform this beautiful house and now I’m more motivated than ever to see this exterior renovation come to life.  Thoughts, questions, concerns… let’s hear them! #exteriorrenovation #paintedbrick
